.TH NHOGET 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhoget \- unified download tool for nhopkg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhoget
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIURL\fR [\fIDEST\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhoget\fR is the unified download system for the nhopkg package manager. It
downloads files via HTTP/HTTPS (using GNU wget, curl, or BusyBox wget), clones
VCS repositories (git, svn, hg), and auto-detects source types from URL
prefixes. It serves as the transparent download backend for nhopkg's build,
install, and update operations and can also be used as a standalone CLI tool.
.SH COMMANDS
Exactly one command must be specified.
.TP
.B download
Download a file via HTTP/HTTPS. Saves to \fIDEST\fR or derives the filename
from the URL. Supports hash verification with \fB\-\-hash\fR.
.TP
.B clone
Clone a VCS repository to \fIDEST\fR (defaults to the basename of the URL).
Use \fB\-\-type\fR to specify the VCS type (default: git).
.TP
.B fetch
Auto-detect the source type from the URL and download or clone. For URLs
with \fBgit+\fR, \fBsvn+\fR, \fBhg+\fR prefixes or \fB.git\fR suffix,
the appropriate VCS is used. Plain URLs are treated as tarballs and are
automatically extracted.
.TP
.B patch
Download a patch or diff file and save it to the current directory using
the original filename from the URL.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Save output to a specific file (download command only).
.TP
.B \-O, \-\-output-dir \fIDIR\fR
Save output to a directory.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-resume
Resume a partial download.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-timeout \fISECS\fR
Timeout in seconds (default: 20).
.TP
.B \-\-retries \fIN\fR
Number of retries (default: 3).
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B \-\-hash \fITYPE:VALUE\fR
Verify the downloaded file against the given hash (e.g. sha256:...).
.TP
.B \-\-type \fITYPE\fR
Force source type: \fBtarball\fR, \fBgit\fR, \fBsvn\fR, or \fBhg\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-ref \fIREF\fR
VCS reference: tag, branch, commit (git), or revision (svn).
.TP
.B \-\-depth \fIN\fR
Shallow clone depth (git only).
.TP
.B \-\-backend \fIBACKEND\fR
Force download backend: \fBwget\fR, \fBcurl\fR, \fBwget-bb\fR, or \fBauto\fR
(default: auto, which prefers GNU wget for backward compatibility).
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show a brief help message.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show the version number.
.SH URL PREFIXES
.TP
.B git+\fIURL\fR
Git repository (also matches \fI*.git\fR).
.TP
.B svn+\fIURL\fR
Subversion repository.
.TP
.B hg+\fIURL\fR
Mercurial repository.
.TP
.B \fIURL\fR (no prefix)
Tarball or plain file; auto-extracted if the filename ends in
\fI.tar.zst\fR, \fI.tar.xz\fR, \fI.tar.bz2\fR, \fI.tar.gz\fR, \fI.zip\fR,
or \fI.AppImage\fR.
.SH BACKEND PRIORITY
When \fB\-\-backend auto\fR (the default), the first available backend is
used in this order:
.IP 1. 3
GNU wget (full-featured)
.IP 2. 3
curl
.IP 3. 3
BusyBox wget (limited but functional; retries are implemented via a manual
loop since the \fB-t\fR flag is unavailable)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NHOGET_DOWNLOAD_LIB
Path to \fIlibnhopkg_download\fR. If unset, the installed default
(\fI@prefix@/lib/nhopkg/libnhopkg_download\fR) is used.
.TP
.B NHOGET_BACKEND
Download backend override (wget|curl|wget-bb|auto).
.TP
.B NHOGET_TIMEOUT
Connection timeout in seconds (default: 20).
.TP
.B NHOGET_RETRIES
Number of download retries (default: 3).
.TP
.B NHOGET_RESUME
Set to "yes" to enable resume of partial downloads.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/nhopkg/libnhopkg_download
Download library (sourced by nhoget and nhopkg).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
General error (invalid arguments, download failure, hash mismatch, etc.).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR nhopkg-src (8),
.BR nhopkg-repos (8),
.BR nhopkg.conf (5)
.SH AUTHOR
Jaime Gil de Sagredo Luna <jaimegildesagredo@gmail.com>
